node.title: Live - Final COVID-19 update before Christmas coming soon as Kiwis set off on travel
node.content: ["The Ministry of Health will shortly deliver the final COVID-19 update before Christmas as hundreds of thousands of Kiwis clock off work, many travelling to other parts of the country.", "There were 56 new community cases of COVID-19 on Thursday, with no new Omicron detections in MIQ and no new cases found in Hutt Valley, where a single infection was recorded on Wednesday.", "10:50am - Kia ora, good morning, and welcome to Newshub's live updates for Friday.", "The COVID-19 update is expected to be delivered at 1pm. It will be the final statement until Boxing Day, with no new data to be provided on Christmas Day.", "It comes amid concerns that Kiwis travelling out of COVID-19 hotspots could be taking the virus with them as they set off to lower vaccinated areas, like Northland and Tairawhiti.\u00a0"]
